---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Support | NextMetro"
  description="Get help with NextMetro, the iPhone and Apple Watch app for timing your WMATA commute."
>
  <section class="section tight content-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">Support</p>
    <h1>Help for your next ride.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Need help with setup, train predictions, Watch sync, or leave alerts?
      Send the details and we will help get NextMetro back on track.
    </p>

    <div class="contact-panel panel">
      <h2>Email Support</h2>
      <p>
        Send a note to <a href="mailto:support@nextmetro.app">support@nextmetro.app</a>
        with your device model, app version, station, route, and what happened.
      </p>
      <a class="button primary" href="mailto:support@nextmetro.app">Contact Support</a>
    </div>

    <div class="contact-panel panel">
      <h2>Beta Access</h2>
      <p>
        NextMetro is starting with a focused WMATA commute beta. If you want to
        test it, include your iPhone model, Apple Watch model, usual station,
        and destination.
      </p>
      <a class="button secondary" href="mailto:support@nextmetro.app?subject=NextMetro%20Beta">Join Beta</a>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Common Questions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          If setup is blocked, sync your commute settings from iPhone to Apple
          Watch.
        </li>
        <li>
          If train times look stale, check your network connection and reopen the
          app to refresh predictions.
        </li>
        <li>
          If alerts are missing, confirm notifications are enabled for NextMetro
          in your device settings.
        </li>
        <li>
          If your station or direction is not available yet, include the station
          name and route in your support email.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
